    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="496" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Runyon</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 224.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 185, of the 5th ultimo,
                            relative to the apprehended danger to trade between the United States
                            and Germany, if the grounds of complaint of the latter as to the special
                            duty on sugar be not removed, has been received and read with
                            attention.</p>
                <p>You have doubtless learned from the public press that the sugar
                            differential repeal bill has passed the House of Representatives.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                                    Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
